            <p>The name Waikiki means spouting waters and refers to the freshwater rivers that once used to flow towards the ocean. Previously, the coastal area of Waikiki in South Oahu once engaged a more significant size which included Manoa and Palolo Valleys. Waikiki was designated as the first government center in Hawaii in 1450. </p>

            <h5>Na Pali Coast State Wilderness Park</h5>
            <p>The Na Pali Coastline on Kauai is one of the most beautiful places to visit in your lifetime. Besides being the best place to see in Hawaii, this coastline region is also super rich in Hawaiian cultural history. This area was home to Hawaiian Ali'i and is famous for its flowing waterfalls and freshwater rivers. The site is abundant with Hawaiian flora and fauna and an excess supply of natural food sources like taro, sweet potatoes, breadfruit, fresh fish, and many more. The Na Pali Coastline can only be reached by foot or ocean vessel, as a result of which it remains isolated. </p>

